<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-07-08T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-07-08T12:00:00-05:00" n="512" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d512">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">825.00 Revolutions/145: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_CWS1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Culbertson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-07-08T12:00:00-05:00">July 8,
                                    1932—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 1:11 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>126. <persName corresp="#p_DCG1">Dávila</persName> is Provisional
                            President this morning but with uncertain and probably short tenure.
                                <persName corresp="#p_IGC1">Ibañez</persName> is holding aloof. His
                            support is increasing and his policy seems to be to wait until public
                            opinion demands his return to power. Belief is general that this will be
                            soon.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_CWS1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Culbertson</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>